ref: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.285, p.125 (2012)
title: Investigation of the alpha-particle induced nuclear reactions on natural molybdenum

x4freetext: Investigation of the alpha-particle induced nuclear
reactions on natural molybdenum

x4codes.hlp: Institute for Nuclear Research (ATOMKI), Debrecen, Hungary

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.285, p.125 (2012)

x4freetext: High purity commercial metal foils
Two stacks were
irradiated at the external beams of the VUB CGR 560
(Brussels) cyclotron. High purity commercial metal
foils of natMo (12 micron) and natCu foils (12.3
micron) for monitoring were stacked together. The
beam current was kept low and constant, initial beam
energy was up to 40 MeV. The effective mean energy
for each foil was determined using the energy range
formula and tables of Andersen and Ziegler. The decay
data and the Q-values were taken from NUDAT2. The
activity of the foils was measured without chemical
separation by high resolution gamma-ray spectrometry.

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Nuclear Data Services (Doc. series of NDS), No.1211 (2001)

x4freetext: The initial uncertainty of the beam energy
was +-0.3MeV. The uncertainty on the energy was
estimated from the uncertainties of the energy of the
primary beam, from the uncertainty of the thicknesses
of the different stopping media in the stack and from
the energy straggling. The uncertainty of the energy
increased from 0.3 MeV for the first foil of a stack
to just below 1 MeV at the stack end.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The uncertainty of the cross-sections was
estimated from the independent relative errors of the
linearly contributing processes (number of the
bombarding particles, number of the target nuclei,
decay data, detector efficiency and peak area).
The uncertainties on the absolute cross- sections were
in the range of 12-20%.
The experimental data were compared to the
results of the theoretical model codes: TALYS (results
were taken from TENDL-2011 database), ALICE and
EPIRE-3.1.
The measured experimental data were compared to
those found in the literature.
Fitted excitation functions were used for
determination of integral physical yields.
